            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>Then you see that Andre Dawkins and Mason Plumlee logged 13 minutes each, and Ryan Kelly was in for seven, and it seems to fit the pattern. (We&rsquo;re also conveniently ignoring the fact that Kyle Singler, Jon Scheyer and Nolan Smith played 38, 38 and 36 minutes, respectively.) Coach K wanted to beat Georgetown, but he recognized that the short turnaround made it difficult, and he wasn&rsquo;t going to sacrifice ACC games to win a big out-of-conference matchup. &nbsp;</p>
<p>At least, I hope that&rsquo;s what it means. Because the alternatives&mdash;a late-season slide is imminent, Georgetown really is that much better than Duke&mdash;are really depressing.</p>
<p>Hey, at least UNC&rsquo;s been awful!</p>

